==English==
===Noun===
'''botulism'''
{{wikipedia}}
#A rare but serious medical condition cuased by ingesting the nerve [[toxin]] [[botulin]], that is produced by the bacterium Clostridium botulinum.  The [[bacteria]] is [[anerobic]] and so grows only in the absense of oxygen, such as in canned foods.  Contaminated cans bulger from released pressure.  While modern industrial [[canning]] rarely allows botulism to occur it was at one time a significant danger and can still pose a threat in home canned products.